HEADWORD: Longheaded
<hw>Long"head"ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having unusual foresight or sagacity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>having a relatively long head with a cephalic index
of under 75. Opposite of <ant>brachycephalic</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> dolichocephalic, dolichocranal,
dolichocranic.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p> -- <wordforms><wf>Long"-head`ed*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Longhorn</ent>⟦br⟧
